10. Thai What Now?

The food in restaurants is ridiculously cheap in Sri Lanka – making the price listed on menus pretty much a joke. We asked our taxi driver how much it would have been to get taken from our hotel to the airport… and he said less than 2000 rupees (S$20). 25 minutes. Our cab ride from the airport to the Blue Sky Villa cost over 4000 rupees (S$40). The extra money we threw to our driver was spit in the face. At least you could see him offended.

11. Rough Play by the Shore

There are little places to sit right on the beach at a lot of the towns around badagri beach. The chairs are covered in sand, have no cushions, back slightly and you’re done for. Lower the charge, and I’m still not sitting there. Some guy decided to have a bottle throwing at the rocks throwing contest. After his second throw, he fell and hit his back so hard that the whole beach turned and stared. Then the guy in the next chair thought it would be a good idea to pick up a rock. And throw it.

The dude’s back recovered fast. Not the rock – the dudes back.
